{
  "stem": "8.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "But we were-- one, one day, we were taken to a bath.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "We were taken to a bath about once a week or once every other week.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "And as we were marching, we were go-- we were going by a German officer's area.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "And I saw a swimming pool.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "And I jumped out of the line, and I dove into the swimming pool.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "And I swam across the pool, and I got back.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "And they didn't shoot me, and I survived.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "But of course, my mother almost died.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "I mean, it was such an irr-- irresponsible act from my part.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "But I was young, and I, I needed to be alive.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 79,
      "text": "And I did that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 80,
      "text": "Another important event-- we went another time also to the bathes, and we saw my uncle working with the bricks there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 81,
      "text": "He knew that we were alive, and he was hoping that he would one day see us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 82,
      "text": "And he prepared-- on our way back, he prepared for us some bread and a sweater for me.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 83,
      "text": "And, and he ran out, and he gave us a kiss and a hug.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 84,
      "text": "And unfortunately, he didn't survive.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 85,
      "text": "He was-- he stayed in the Auschwitz until they, they eventually-- they exploded the crematorium, and that's where he died.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had-- we had a dress.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a gray dress with-- no longer, we didn't-- we had-- because we had on-- our numbers on our arm, we no longer had our numbers on the dress.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we received a wooden platform canvas shoe that we then-- which lasted throughout our-- there were everyday bombings and air raids in Auschwitz-- not at Auschwitz, but around Auschwitz, the factories there.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember I used to say, well, this is a good sign.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
